snippet.title: (No EAS) Hondo, TX - Texas AMBER Alert - 12/21/2021
snippet.description:
Product: https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=CAECRP&e=202112220330

BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE CORPUS CHRISTI TX
930 PM CST TUE DEC 21 2021

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THE MEDINA COUNTY SHERIFF'S OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR LUCAS WRIGHT,
WHITE, MALE, 9 YEARS OLD, 4 FEET 5 INCHES, 70 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR,
HAZEL EYES, AND WEARING ALL GREEN OUTERWEAR, LL BEAN
ORANGE/BLUE/WHITE UNDER-COAT, GRAY ADIDAS SHOES WITH RED BOTTOMS.

THE MEDINA COUNTY SHERIFF'S OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR ARIANA WRIGHT,
WHITE, FEMALE, 8 YEARS OLD, 4 FEET 5 INCHES, 70 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR,
HAZEL EYES, AND WEARING ALL GREEN OUTERWEAR, LL BEAN PURPLE
UNDER-COAT, BROWN BOOTS WITH A CAMO LEAF TOP.

THE MEDINA COUNTY SHERIFF'S OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR JONATHAN
WRIGHT, WHITE, MALE, 11 YEARS OLD, 4 FEET 8 INCHES, 80 POUNDS, BROWN
HAIR, BROWN EYES, AND WEARING ALL GREEN OUTERWEAR, LL BEAN BRIGHT
BLUE UNDER-COAT, GRAY ADIDAS SHOES WITH RED BOTTOMS.

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR JONATHAN ALEXANDER WRIGHT, WHITE, MALE, 40
YEARS OLD, 5 FEET 9 INCHES, 170 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN EYES AND
POSSIBLY WEAING A GREEN JACKET OR HOODIE, IN CONNECTION WITH THEIR
ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM AT 3:45 PM ON DECEMBER 20, 2021 NEAR
CR 366 AND FM 2676 IN HONDO, TX ON FOOT.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THESE CHILDREN TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER. 

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE MEDINA
COUNTY SHERIFF'S OFFICE AT 8 3 0 7 4 1 6 1 5 3.

$$

snippet.title: Amber Alert-the sound of an Amber Alert
snippet.description:
i used my webcam to get this clip (sorry if i don't get all of the footage, i just wanted to get the Amber Alert sound that plays in North Texas when an Amber Alert is issued in which it follows the EAS sound when the North Texas EAS is activated for an Amber Alert.) i got this off of Fox 4 Dallas (KDFW-TV) i sure it also aired on My Network TV 27 (KDFI-TV). for those who complain that the Amber Alert itself is scary, just listen to this sound that is heard here in this Video.

Due to chain letters, spammers, and trolls who start flame wars and call people racial slurs, all comments will be approved by me only.

snippet.title: Tennessee AMBER Alert on WXK47 & 89.5 WETS-FM - 2/19/20 (EAS #3,757 & 3,758)
snippet.description:
UPDATE: March 6th, 2020... The Tennessee Bureau of Investigation says authorities have found what they believe to be the remains of missing East Tennessee 15-month-old Evelyn Boswell.

Sullivan County Sheriff's detectives found the remains during a search of a property in Blountville belonging to a family member of the child's mother, Megan "Maggie" Boswell, in Blountville.

The remains will be sent for an autopsy and a positive identification.

Tennessee Bureau of Investigation issued an Amber Alert for the child on Feb. 18. Evelyn hadn't been seen for about a month before family members reported her as missing to police. One day later, the Amber Alert was issued.

Maggie Boswell and the child's grandmother, Angela Boswell, were both arrested in the case. Maggie was accused of giving false reports during the investigation. Angela was arrested and charged with possession of stolen property after being found in a vehicle of interest.

snippet.title: Amber Alert on the Andy Griffith show. Mandela Effect?
snippet.description: Barney Fife mentions "Amber alert" on The Andy Griffith show.  Anyone ever hear of the Mandela Effect? I have, and I think this might be an example.  The Amber Alert was named after a little girl named Amber who was kidnapped and murdered in Texas in 1996. She was born in 1986 and was just 9 years old when she went missing many Years after this show was televised. So why does Barney Fife use the phrase named after a little girl in the future, and practically uses it in the proper context. Its normally used as an emergency alert for missing or abducted children but he uses it in an emergency situation on the show. Close enough.   What do you think. Do your own research on the show and the Amber Alert and tell me what you think.

snippet.title: Lite da film dell'orrore tra Johnny Depp e Amber Heard
snippet.description: Dettagli da film horror emergono dall'audio di una lite tra Johnny Depp e Amber Heard pubblicato dal Daily Mail. “Non riesco a trovare il tuo dito!” - urla il medico dell'attore, colpito con una bottiglia di vodka dalla moglie. Il litigio risale a marzo 2015, in Australia e l'audio esiste perché i due registravano tutto per la terapia di coppia. Tra gli ex coniugi è in corso una battaglia legale con reciproche accuse gravissime di violenze domestiche

snippet.title: | Dulce Maria Alvarez  | 5 Month FBI Amber Alert Update |Actively Working The Case | New Jersey
snippet.description:
#DULCEALVAREZ #AmberAlert #FBIUpdate

NEW JERSEY – The FBI has provided an update in the nearly five-month Amber Alert search for 5-year-old Dulce Maria Alavez, offering hope in the long investigation just as searchers have begun to express dismay.

A spokeswoman for the family, Jackie Rodriguez, even expressed frustration in an interview with Patch that Dulce's mother has not been more forthcoming about what she may or may not know in the missing persons case.

"I always ask her, 'Is there anything you're afraid of saying?' " Rodriguez said, who has previously suggested that Noema Alavez may know more than she's let on. "She could be trying to protect her daughter and she's scared" of saying anything.

The FBI, meanwhile, remains involved in the Bridgeton area investigation and will stay involved, Special Agent in Charge Gregory W. Ehrie told Patch. "We will not stop looking for that child until there is a resolution," she said.

As for Rodriguez's comments about how Dulce's mother may be "scared" to reveal information, Ehrie said: "In general, when a person is threatened in connection with an FBI matter, they should report it. Witness tampering is a crime."

The FBI's Newark office has dedicated "countless hours of manpower" in the search for Dulce, Ehrie said. The FBI works closely with the Bridgeton police chief and the Cumberland County prosecutor "in the effort to bring this child home," he said.

The FBI included Dulce on a social media push for National Missing

snippet.title: Amber Alert "Brajaean Sledge"
snippet.description:
KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) - Police in Kansas City have recovered the vehicle believed to be used in the abduction of a 15-year-old Kansas City girl on Thursday.

Brajean Sledge was abducted from a home in the 2700 block of Elmwood Avenue after a man entered her grandfather's home and shot her 60-year-old grandfather.

An Amber Alert has been issued in both Missouri and Kansas for Sledge.

Police say Sledge's grandfather was taken to an area hospital and is in serious but stable condition.

The suspect, who could be with Sledge, is described as a black male between the ages of 18-20. He should be considered armed and dangerous. 

"We believe she is with the shooting suspect and we believe she is also in danger," said Kansas City police officer Jake Becchina. "They were last seen northbound from here in a 2017 KIA forte license plate MB5 G5B."

At about 8 a.m. Friday, officers recovered the suspect vehicle near 112th Street and Bennington Avenue.

Detectives are actively searching the area and are processing the contents of the vehicle.

Sledge was last seen wearing a white V-neck t-shirt and dark pants. Police say she has black hair with a blonde weave.

The suspect is described as a black male in his late teens last seen wearing a gray hoodie.

Neighbors say they heard gunfire in the area and were shocked to find out what happened.

"If I was the parents, I would be worried as well," neighbor Montay McKinney said. "I know it's a tough situation for the family. I send my condolences."

Police delayed making a statewide Amber Alert Thursday because they believed the girl was still in the Kansas City area. They have since expanded their search.

It should be noted that Sledge goes by multiple different names and aliases:

Brajaean Sledge

Brajean Sweeten

Bre-Shawn

Brayshawn

Brajean

Rayshawn

Anyone who sees Sledge or has information about the suspect or their whereabouts is asked to call 911.

snippet.title: Both Indiana children located after Amber Alert found dead in mother’s car
snippet.description:
FT. WAYNE, Ind. (WKRC) - An AMBER Alert was cancelled for two children in Fort Wayne, Indiana. 

Local 12 News has learned that both 7-year-old Lilian Hernandez and 6-year-old Rene Pasztor were found dead in the backseat of their mother's car. 

Local 12's sister station, WSBT, reported an officer was stopped outside the police department around 5:30 p.m. Monday, September 26, by the children's biological mother, Amber Pasztor. She told the officer there were two dead children in the back seat of the car. 

Deputies believed the children were in  extreme danger after being abducted by Pasztor Monday morning. She did not have custody.



The following release was issued by the Elkhart Police Department Monday night, September 26:

On Monday September 26, 2016 at 12:51 PM the Allen County Sheriff’s Department issued an Amber Alert with regards to two missing children, which they believed to be in danger. At the time of the Amber Alert, it was believed the children were abducted by their mother.

On Monday September 26, 2016 at 5:25 PM an officer who was walking out of the Elkhart Police Department, on Marion Street, was stopped by a subject driving a vehicle. The subject driving the vehicle reported to the officer there were two (2) deceased subjects inside the vehicle. Upon examining the vehicle officers located two deceased juveniles in the backseat of the vehicle.

Upon further investigation officers discovered the vehicle the subject was driving matched the vehicle information provided in the Amber Alert; a gold Mercury.

The female driver of the vehicle has been identified as Amber Pasztor. Further investigation is underway to better understand the circumstances surrounding the children’s death.

At this time the two juveniles located inside the vehicle are believed to be Liliana Hernandez and Rene Pasztor. However formal identification of the two juveniles will be done by the Coroner’s Office at a later time.

We are currently looking trying to determine the whereabouts of one Frank Macomber who may have additional information.

At this point in the investigation detectives from the Elkhart Police Department Homicide Unit are working with detectives from the Allen County Sheriff’s Department Homicide unit.

The following release was issued earlier in the day:

The Allen County Sheriff is investigating the abduction of two children from Fort Wayne, Indiana.

Liliana Hernandez is a 7-year-old white female, 3 ft, 4 in tall, long brown hair, brown eyes and was last seen wearing a black nightgown.

Rene Pasztor is a 6-year-old white male, 3 ft tall, short brown hair, brown eyes and was last seen wearing black shorts.

The children were last seen at 6:21 am EDT in Fort Wayne, IN and are believed to be in extreme danger.

Fort Wayne, Indiana is 125 miles north of Indianapolis, Indiana.

Allen County Sheriff believes the children were likely abducted by their non-custodial mother Amber Pasztor a 29-year-old white female, 5 ft, 6 in tall, 250 lbs., with long blonde hair. Suspect vehicle is a Mercury, Mystique, Tan in color.

If you have any information on these children, contact the Allen County Sheriff at 260-449-7661.

snippet.title: Child Abduction Emergency (AMBER ALERT) Houston, Texas The Scariest AMBER ALERT I've ever heard
snippet.description:
Event: Child Abduction Emergency
Sender Name: Houston Police Department
Issued: 2019-10-21T20:38:56-04:00
Expires: 2019-10-22T19:38:56-04:00
WEA Text: Houston, TX AMBER Alert: LIC/LXR1070 (TX) 2007 Gray Toyota Corolla 4-door sedan
Description: Texas Center for the Missing has issued a Houston Regional Amber Alert for the Houston Police Department for endangered missing 3-year old Clayber Victor Larosa-Reyes. The suspect, Ingrid Urbina-Centeno, is the ex-girlfriend of the mother of the 3-year-old child. At 12:15 PM today, 10-21-2019, the suspect took the 3 year old child. The suspect told the mother of the child, Maria Garcia-Reyes, “I’m going to kill your son so it hurts you the way it hurt me when you left me”. The suspect then left with the child. Investigators believe that there is a threat to the child’s welfare at this time. The suspect was driving a gray, 4-door Toyota Corolla, with Texas License Plate LXR1070. The mother left in pursuit of the suspect and the mother has not been heard from since as well. Also missing is Claybers’ mother, Maria Susana Garcia-Reyes. They were all last see in SW Houston near Gessner Rd. and Bellaire Blvd. Anyone with information regarding the missing child or mother is asked to immediately call the Houston Police Department at 713-308-3600.
Instruction: NO FURTHER INSTRUCTIONS PROVIDED.
Link to more Info: www.missingkids.org
Urgency: Immediate
Severity: Severe
Certainty: Observed
Categories: Other

snippet.title: Amber Alert sent out for 6-year-old allegedly abducted by 17-year-old in Georgia
snippet.description:
You may have heard an alert go off on your phone Monday morning. Right now, the search is on for a missing 6-year-old who was allegedly abducted in Georgia on Sunday. An Amber Alert went out around 4:30 a.m. Monday. Right now, it's believed that the child was abducted by a 17-year-old, according to the Center For Missing and Exploited Children. The alert states the 6-year-old may be in extreme danger. According to the Habersham County Sheriff's Office Facebook page, 17-year-old Estephanie Ramirez and 6-year-old Celesta Ramirez were last seen Sunday at 11 a.m. in a gold 2010 Honda Pilot.

Subscribe to 13WMAZ for exclusive content: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRNf0_t4Qo5eojj8sSvd_8A  

13WMAZ News is the #1 station for news and weather in the Central Georgia area, serving people in Dublin, Macon, Milledgeville and Warner Robins.

snippet.title: Kentucky Amber Alert (3/25/20) (EAS 2336)
snippet.description:
THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE
KENTUCKY EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT AGENCY LOUISVILLE KENTUCKY. AT THE REQUEST OF THE KENTUCKY STATE POLICE...THE KENTUCKY EMERGENCY ALERT SYSTEM IS ACTIVATED TO ASSIST IN THE BROADCAST OF AN AMBER ALERT.

AN AMBER ALERT HAS BEEN DECLARED...REPEATING...AN AMBER ALERT HAS BEEN DECLARED.

INCIDENT SUMMARY: SUSAN BLANCHARD IS THE GRANDMOTHER AND LEGAL GUARDIAN OF TWO SEVEN YEAR OLD TWINS, ISABELLA AND AUDRIANA BLANCHARD. NEELY BLANCHARD CAME TO VISIT THE TWINS ON FRIDAY MARCH 20 2020. NEELY TOOK THE TWINS TO A FRIENDS RESIDENCE IN DAWSON SPRINGS KENTUCKY. ACCORDING TO THE FRIEND THAT RESIDES IN DAWSON SPRINGS, NEELY HASN`T BEEN SEEN OR HEARD FROM SINCE MONDAY MARCH 23 2020. SUSAN BELIEVES NEELY BLANCHARD MAY BE EN ROUTE TO SOUTH CAROLINA WHERE HER 11 YEAR OLD DAUGHTER RESIDES WITH HER GRANDMOTHER. NEELY HAS A HISTORY OF MENTAL ILLNESS FURTHER COMPOUNDED BY THE CORONAVIRUS PANDEMIC. SHE IS IN POSSESSION OF A HANDGUN. SHE IS DRIVING A BLACK 2014 FORD ESCAPE WITH FLORIDA LICENCE PLATE E C L A U S E

VICTIMS: ISABELLA BLANCHARD. A WHITE FEMALE AGED 7 YEARS OLD. SHE HAS GREEN EYES AND BROWN HAIR AND IS THREE FEET EIGHT INCHES TALL WEIGHING 60 POUNDS.

AUDRIANNA BLANCHARD. A WHITE FEMALE AGED 7 YEARS OLD. SHE HAS GREEN EYES AND BROWN HAIR AND IS FOUR FEET TALL WEIGHING 75 POUNDS.

SUSPECT: NEELY BLANCHARD. A WHITE FEMALE AGED 33 YEARS OLD. SHE HAS HAZEL EYES AND BROWN HAIR AND IS FIVE FEET EIGHT INCHES TALL WEIGHING 140 POUNDS.

VEHICLE: A BLACK 2014 FORD ESCAPE WITH FLORIDA LICENCE PLATE READING
E C L A U S E

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ALERT PLEASE CONTACT THE KENTUCKY STATE POLICE.
———————————————————

snippet.title: SUSPICIOUS- TN AMBER Alert 5yo Summer Wells- 'Growing Concerns'
snippet.description:
Local, state and federal authorities are investigating the disappearance of a 5-year-old girl who is missing in Tennessee. 5-year-old Summer Wells was last seen walking from her home Tuesday evening in the Beech Creek community of Hawkins County. Authorities initially issued an endangered child alert, but as of Wednesday upgraded it to an AMBER Alert, citing “new information and growing concern,”

Police held a press conference on Wednesday detailing the search efforts and the challenges facing investigators, but have said very little about the circumstances of Summer’s disappearance. Police have not publicly identified a suspect or issued a vehicle description, details that often accompany AMBER Alerts.

Hawkins County Sheriff Ronnie Lawson said at Wednesday’s news conference that the Tennessee Bureau of Investigation and the FBI were aiding local authorities in the search, which involves dense, challenging terrain. Lawson also said at the press conference that investigators are having difficulty communicating because of spotty cell phone service in the remote area of eastern Tennessee.

“What makes it so hard is communication between boots on the ground, searchers in the woods and the different agencies. We aren’t like in these towns where they’ve got a lot of cell service,” Lawson said

Lawson said that Summer’s family is cooperating, and that it was too early in the investigation to determine if foul play was involved in the little girl’s disappearance.

Summer Wells is described as 3-feet tall with blonde hair, recently cut short. When she was last seen, she was wearing a pink shirt and grey shorts. Anyone with information or who sees her should immediately call 911.

This video is for educational purposes.

snippet.title: Amber Alert | America Is Great
snippet.description:
David's cell phone started vibrating in the middle of the night. He woke up right away and nervously reached to his nightstand. He always set his cell phone to vibrate and charged it next to his bed when he went to sleep. David looked at the time on his cell phone. It was two in the morning. The only time someone contacted him at that hour was when there was an emergency.
 
He read the message on his cell phone. It was an emergency. The text message said that a little boy had been kidnapped near where David lived. The boy had been taken into an orange Honda Civic. The text message also gave the license plate number of the car. There was also a picture of the little boy and a written description of what the boy was wearing when he was kidnapped. The boy's name was Adam.

David didn't feel like he could do anything at two o'clock in the morning. He went back to sleep. In the morning, however, he woke up thinking about the message and about the boy. David had never heard about an Amber Alert before. He decided to look it up on his computer. He learned that the Amber Alert system is an emergency broadcast system used to let people know when a child is abducted. It was named for a little girl named Amber Hagerman, who was kidnapped when riding her bike in Texas. Little Amber was found dead later.

The news made David feel sad and angry, but he also felt like now he could do something to help. He decided to stay aware to see if he saw a boy or a car matching the description in the Amber Alert.
-------------------------------------------

snippet.title: Amber Alert: 2 North Texas teens abducted, believed to be in grave danger
snippet.description:
Amber Alert: 2 North Texas teens abducted, believed to be in grave danger
An Amber Alert has been issued for two North Texas teenagers last seen southeast of Dallas early Sunday morning

Police from Seagoville, a city southeast of Dallas on State Highway 175, believe Devany Betancourt, 16, and Marina Nelson, 17, are in “grave or immediate danger” after their abduction. The alert, issued by the Texas Department of Public Safety, does not include suspect information

Betancourt is described by police as:

Hispanic girl
5’2″
110 pounds
Brown eyes with black hair
Last seen wearing a gold and pink shirt, jeans, brown boots, a gold chain with a bull and two gold rings
Nelson is described by police as:

White girl
5’9″
130 pounds
Green eyes and brown hair
Last seen wearing an orange shirt, gray sweatshirt and shorts
If you have seen either girl, call the Seagoville Police Department at 972-287-6815

snippet.title: AMBER ALERT 🚨 EVELYN MAE BOSWELL - 15 Month Girl from Tennessee - PLEASE SHARE
snippet.description:
AMBER ALERT 🚨 EVELYN MAE BOSWELL - 15 Month Girl from Tennessee - PLEASE SHARE

IMPORTANT! Amber alert issued yesterday February 19th, 2020 for little missing 15 month old, Evelyn Boswell. Last seen on Dec 26th, 2019 and reported missing on Feb 18th, 2020. 

Little Evelyn Mae Boswell hasn't been seen in 2 months. Her mother, Maggie Boswell (also known as Megan Boswell) has conflicting stories that don't add up. 

The TBI and FBI are helping in the search for little Evelyn. She was last seen wearing a pink outfit, pink shoes, and a pink bow. 

Email me: itsacrimeandashame@gmail.com

#evelynboswell #itsacrime #amberalert

snippet.title: Amber alert GLMM/GLMV || Emotional Mini movie || Read desc for story explanation-
snippet.description:
Henlo :D
I hope you enjoyed this short GLMM/GLMV ❤️ 
I’m so sorry if its bad I’m a beginner I’m not a professional yet ;(

Here’s an explanation:
~~~
There are 2 siblings, One named “Maddie” (The oldest one with a hair down) that is 11 years old and “Kenzie” (The short one with tied hair) That is 9 years old.

They went to the park, Before they go in, Kenzie told her sister that she loves her and she’ll always be in her side no matter what. Maddie told her sister to promise that shell never leave her, she promised.

When they went in, the played allot of games, they got a little bored so they have decided to play hide and seek, Maddie wasn’t feeling good about it but she went with it. Kenzie looked for places to hide but she didn’t find a good spot, she went far from her sister, But she didn’t know where she was heading.

Kenzie went to an unknown place, she saw a k!dnapper with a dead body, when the k!dnapper saw Kenzie she ran to catch her. 

Maddie was done counting and went to search for Kenzie but unfortunately she didn’t find her anywhere. She went to her parents and told them about Kenzie. 
Mean while with Kenzie, the k!dnapper took her and tried to put her in a chair and tie her up, but Kenzie kept making it difficult by moving the chair. When Kenzie got hurt in her feet the k!dnapper turned her and sat her down then tied her up.

Maddie was in a search for Kenzie with her parents, she started to have flashback about the sweet moments of Kenzie, she started to be emotional because she realized that someone is really on her side and loved her. 

The k!dnapper decided to call her friends for backup, she didn’t want to murder a 9 year old. Maddie was still searching.

When the k!dnapper’s friends came, she asked what to do with Kenzie, her friend brought poisonous pills with her, they all agreed to poison her.

Her friend held her and opened Kenzie’s mouth so they can put the pill on her mouth, Kenzie accidentally swallowed it and became dizzy. Her friends heard footsteps and ran away. 

Maddie found Kenzie and she hugged her, she thought that Kenzie was alive... When Maddie raised her head she noticed that she was poisoned, Maddie got emotional and ran away she never looked back...
~~~
That’s it :DDD❤️

Mean while with Kenzie, the k!dnapper took her and tried to put her in a chair and tie her up, but Kenzie kept making it difficult by moving the chair. When Kenzie got hurt in her feet the k!dnapper turned her and sat her down then tied her up.

Maddie was in a search for Kenzie with her parents, she started to have flashback about the sweet moments of Kenzie, she started to be emotional because she realized that someone is really on her side and loved her. 

The k!dnapper decided to call her friends for backup, she didn’t want to murder a 9 year old. Maddie was still searching.

When the k!dnapper’s friends came, she asked what to do with Kenzie, her friend brought poisonous pills with her, they all agreed to poison her.

Her friend held her and opened Kenzie’s mouth so they can put the pill on her mouth, Kenzie accidentally swallowed it and became dizzy. Her friends heard footsteps and ran away. 

Maddie found Kenzie and she hugged her, she thought that Kenzie was alive... When Maddie raised her head she noticed that she was poisoned, Maddie got emotional and ran away she never looked back...
~~~

snippet.title: Amber Alert Trailer
snippet.description:
Amber Alert

Summary: Anna is taken from her home to live out a sick game that a guy has been playing for the last ten years. With no certainty that anyone is looking for her, and seemingly hours away from home, she's forced to play house wife with a man that has had twelve other 'wives'. 

Each of them now dead. 

From breaking a rule, and making another as they escape. With 12 rules and the obvious exits blocked, from how the previous girls escaped. Is the only way out to play along and be a 'loving wife' or will she die during the chase? Would anyone know what happened to her or would she be labeled as a runaway? Where is she in the first place?

Link to Story: http://www.wattpad.com/story/1657022-amber-alert

Link to my account to make trailers: www.wattpad.com/user/TaylorMonet 
or
www.wattpad.com/user/StolenGlances

snippet.title: Suspect wanted in triple homicide, Amber Alert in St. Louis County fatally shoots himself
snippet.description:
ST. LOUIS COUNTY, Mo. - The man wanted in an early morning Amber Alert and triple homicide of a mother and her two children in St. Louis County has died after shooting himself, multiple police sources have confirmed with 5 On Your Side.

Sources told reporter Christine Byers that officers were trying to arrest Bobby McCulley III on Clinton Street in the Old North St. Louis neighborhood in north city when he shot himself while sitting inside a car.

The investigation first started at 11:32 p.m. Thursday when a call came in for a shooting in the 4800 block of Lockwig Trail, which is in north county near Florissant.

Officers found a 34-year-old woman, her 13-year-old son and 6-year-old daughter shot to death inside a house, St. Louis County police confirmed. Their names have not been released.

Read more: https://www.ksdk.com/article/news/crime/st-louis-county-triple-homicide-amber-alert/63-1422ab06-e052-41f2-81f6-5da4067e5b04

snippet.title: New bill to improve amber alert system heard by Missouri House committee
snippet.description:
JEFFERSON CITY - Missouri lawmakers hope to pass a bill that would improve the state's amber alert system. A House committee heard the bill, known as Hailey's Law, this afternoon.  The bill has already passed through the Senate, and sponsored by Springfield's Eric Burlison. 

"The system failed a young girl that day," Senator Eric Burlison said. "And this is the result of trying to attempt to find out what failed in that system and how to address it." 

Hailey's law is named after Hailey Owens, a 10-year-old girl who was abducted and killed by Craig Wood In Springfield in 2014.

snippet.description:
Hours after an amber alert was issued for a 3-year-old girl early Monday morning in central Florida, police found her inside a vehicle with Texas plates and arrested four adults inside the car.  The girl,Madeline Mejia,was on the front lawn of her father's home around 6 a.m. when her dad says he forgot his keys and went back in the house to get them. He heard Mejia screaming and saw her being snatched by a man in a black Honda witha temporary Texas license plate, authorities said.  Florida Highway Patrol Lt. Kim Montessaid the...

snippet.title: Amber Heard talks about career roadblocks due bisexual revelation
snippet.description:
Amber Heard talks about career roadblocks due bisexual revelation
‘Danish Girl’ starlet Amber Heard was shocked to see how coming out as bisexual in 2010, impacted her career.

Addressing the second annual Pride and Prejudice Summit in New York, Amber revealed the truth about her sexuality to a reporter.

&ldquo I just answered honestly,” she revealed in her interview that took place seven years ago. “I could tell by the look on this person’s face it was a big deal. My poor publicist! Then I realised the gravity of what I had done and why so many people -studio execs, agents, advisers -did not want this coming before my name. I became attached to a label. So, I watched as I quickly became not actress Amber Heard but out lesbian Amber Heard.”

The warnings given by Hollywood execs did carry some truth within about being stigmatised.

The thirty-year-old actress revealed how it affected her career, stating, “It did impact my career; it was difficult. It was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult; because no one had done it. I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career without a doubt.”

However, her confession was worth the entire struggle she went through. “I’ve never seen myself defined by the person I’m with. I saw myself being in this unique position and having a unique responsibility. So, I bit the bullet,” she stated.

Around that time, she had credits in Zombieland and Pineapple Express under her belt and she was on the rise.

“As a leading lady, there’s a certain amount of wish fulfilment. I was asked ‘How is anyone going to invest in you romantically if they think you’re unavailable?’” she recalled. “I said, ‘Watch me do it.’”

Amber dated artist and photographer Tasya van Ree at that time and they split in 2012, after four years of dating. She fell for The Rum Diary co-star Johnny Depp and they got married. “When I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it’s funny because I was never in part because I was very stubborn, I guess, and also in part because I just didn’t feel it was wrong,” she commented.

She concluded, “I stand here now among many of my romantic leading lady peers who are out and fluid. I’m one of many now, and I’m working. If every gay man that I know personally in Hollywood came out tomorrow, then this would be a nonissue in a month. We have a long way to go.”

Last her, Heard finalised her divorce with Depp and lately, she’s been linked to billionaire Elon Musk.

snippet.title: Cancelled - Found, Now Safe | Amber Alert | 10/05/21 | Leilana Graham
snippet.description:
Leilana was last seen on Sept. 20 in the 10500 block of Rockaway Drive in northeast Houston. The FBI believes she is in danger and is possibly with 22-year-old Sha Kendrick Edward Smith.

Leilana was last seen wearing a white and yellow striped shirt, unknown color pants, black shoes and she was carrying a clear backpack. She has black hair and brown eyes. She weighs about 147 pounds and is approximately 5 feet, 3 inches tall.

Smith is described as being about 6 feet, 1 inch tall, and weighs about 250 pounds with black hair and brown eyes. Authorities said Smith drives a blue 2008 GMC truck with Texas plates: 28809T1. He was last heard from in Houston.

Anyone with information about Leilana’s whereabouts is urged to call the FBI Houston field office at 713-693-5000, option number 2, or call 911.

CAUTION ADVISED: If located do not approach and immediately contact law enforcement.

snippet.title: Fallen Angels - Amber Alert
snippet.description:
This video is dedicated to our Fallen Angels, children everywhere that have fallen victim to abuse and crimes of violence.

Romans 12:19 Dearly beloved, avenge not yourselves, but rather give place unto wrath: for it is written, vengeance is mine; I will repay, saith the Lord.

While talking with my sister one night last Fall she recanted a story that she claimed she had heard on the news. It was about a little girl who had been abducted from her bedroom in the middle of the night while her parents were sleeping in a nearby room. When they woke up the next morning they called the police immediately to report it, however, an Amber Alert was not issued because her Dad was on Welfare and her Mom was a dancer at a local exotic dance club. I was never able to verify the story but the next day I wrote this song and called it Amber Alert.

You can find all of these Fallen Angels pictures and news stories on the Internet.

If you are in need of prayer either email me or add your prayer requests to the comments section and I will pray for you. 

Copyright
George Deveaux

snippet.title: MOM MURDERED & MAJOR IS MISSING! ACTIVE AMBER ALERT!
snippet.description:
There is an active Amber Alert for a missing 3-year-old boy named Major P. Harris. He was last seen on October 14,2021 on 37th and Clark. His mother, Mallery Muenzenberger was found murdered. snippet.title: Amber Hagerman: The History Behind the Amber Alert

snippet.title: Midland radio going off for an AMBER ALERT
snippet.description: First time I’ve heard an alert on my radio that is non-weather related. It will notify you though, because it is a “weather/all hazards” radio. AMBER ALERT was issued around 1:40 earlier this afternoon in Putnam County. Suspect stole the child in McNabb, Illinois, which is about 40 miles north of where I live. Just got news that the baby and suspect were found in Oglesby, IL about an hour later. The suspect is in custody. Thankfully the baby is safe. That tone sounded more eerie than the severe weather alert tone. I don’t know if the alert tones are different for advisories, watches, and warnings, but this was a different tone. Definitely more spooky than the severe weather one.

snippet.title: ‘I’m worried:’ Amber Alert issued 1 week after Milwaukee mother, daughters reported missing
snippet.description:
MILWAUKEE — Saturday, Feb. 15 marked one week since a Milwaukee mother and her two daughters were reported missing — and an Amber Alert was issued.

The Amber Alert noted Amarah “Jerica” Banks, Cameria Banks, and Zaniya Ivery are believed to be missing under suspicious circumstances. They were last believed to be in the company of Arzel Ivery, 25, who was taken into custody.

Cameria Banks is 4 years old, and Zaniya Ivery is 5.

The three were last seen Saturday, Feb. 8 at 1 a.m. near Sherman Boulevard and Florist Avenue.
“I’m worried,” said Valeria Spinner-Banks, who never thought her daughter, Amarah “Jerica” Banks and her grandchildren would be on a national poster. “This is going out to all of the hotels, and police departments, and hospitals.”

The trio has was added to the database for the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children.

“This is horrible,” said Spinner-Banks. “I wouldn’t wish this on my worst enemy. Just horrible,” Spinner-Banks said.

Spinner-Banks has been full of anguish — having not heard from Jerica and her daughters.

“We feel like this is a bad dream,” Spinner-Banks said. “I’m praying and hoping that she is all right and the kids are all right.”
The last time Spinner-Banks saw the three of them was Friday, Feb. 7 — after a funeral for Jerica’s 1-year-old son, Arzel. The boy died from natural causes. Jerica was dropped off at home with the kids — and has not been heard from since.

“It’s not consistent with her,” said Spinner-Banks. “The whole thing isn’t consistent.”
Described as responsible, Jerica has not been to work — nor the kids to school.

“Her life revolves around her family and her children,” Spinner-Banks said. “It’s just not like her, so I know something is wrong.”

Spinner-Banks asked the community to continue to look at and share the pictures — and holding out hope the public can help find them safe.

“We are just trying to keep positive,” Spinner-Banks said. “The family, we are trying to stray strong, but it’s just not that easy, so we need all the help we can get basically.”

Descriptions of the missing

Amarah “Jerica” Banks, 26, was described as a female, black, standing 5′ tall, weighing 130 pounds, with brown eyes, black hair, and unknown clothing.

Cameria Banks, 4, was described as a female, black, standing 2’5″ tall, weighing 50 pounds, with brown eyes, and long, braided black hair. She was last seen wearing a blue coat with stars, a Lion King shirt, and white pants.

Zaniya Ivery, 5, was described as a female, black, standing 2’5″ tall, weighing 50 pounds, with brown eyes, and long black hair. She was last seen wearing a black coat, and a long-sleeved shirt with a picture of a male sibling’s face on it.

Anyone with information was asked to contact the Milwaukee Police Department Sensitive Crimes Division at 414-935-7405

snippet.title: Utah Amber Alert issued for two girls
snippet.description:
Utah Amber Alert issued for two girls

(KUTV) An Utah Amber Alert has been issued for two girls, 4 and 8 years old.
Police are looking for Elizabeth Dinah Coltharp, 8, and Hattie Briella Coltharp, 4. They are believed to be with Samuel Warren Shaffer, 34.
Police said Shaffer was seen with the two girls along with his own two daughters Lillie and Samantha Shaffer. They were seen on foot but it is not known if there is a vehicle involved.
2News will update this story as more information becomes available.
Elizabeth Cotharp, 8, is described as:
4 feet 9 inches tall
45 pounds
Brown hair
Brown eyes
Last seen wearing a blue dress, gray pants under the dress, wearning hiking books which are possibly camouflaged and a camouflaged jacked.
Hattie Briella Coltharp is 4, is described as:
2 feet 10 inches tall
37 pounds
Brown hair
Brown eyes
Last seen wearing blue spandex pants with purple polka dots and short sleeve shirt of an undetermined color
Suspected abductor Samual Warren Shaffer, 34, is described as:
5 feet 10 inches tall
160 pounds
Brown hair
Hazel eyes
Last seen wearing black pants, a black puffy coat, comouflaged boonie hat
A Facebook page called Help us find the Coltharps has information that KUTV can not verify but may be information useful to finding the missing children.
GRANTSVILLE, Utah (ABC4 Utah) An Amber Alert was canceled after it was issued for two girls age 7 and 11 outside Grantsville Wednesday afternoon.  
 
Officials said the girls were taken from 313 S. Cooley St. around 2:15 p.m. Investigators said the father was issued papers that gave temporary custody to the girls mother. When she went to pick them up they were gone.
 
The suspect and father of the children, 53 year old Kenneth Shrewsbury,  was eventually found in Magna. According to family he was visiting his mother when he heard about the alert.
 
According to Grantsville police, the father and mother are in a custody dispute. They said he voluntarily brought is daughters to a Unified Police Department substation in Magna. 
 
Shrewsbury was taken to the Tooele County Jail, but it's unclear what he will be charged with. The girls are back with their mother.

snippet.title: Amber Alert Remains Active for Summer Wells #summerwells
snippet.description:
Amber Alert Remains Active for Summer Wells!!! 



Summer Wells was first reported missing from her family’s home in the Beech Creek community on June 15, and an Amber Alert was issued by the Tennessee Bureau of Investigation the following day. As the search for Summer continues, anyone with any information regarding her whereabouts is asked to call 1-800-TBI-FIND.


Straight from WJHL: 

https://www.wjhl.com/news/local/summer-wells-tn/tbi-amber-alert-for-summer-wells-will-remain-active-until-the-child-is-located/amp/

HAWKINS CO., Tenn. (WJHL) – Over the weekend, many viewers reached out to News Channel 11 asking if the AMBER Alert for Summer Wells, the missing five-year-old from Hawkins County, had been canceled or called off.

“We have no updates to provide other than to say the investigation remains active and ongoing. AMBER Alerts remain active until the child is located.”

Hispanic
5′ tall
115 pounds
Brown hair and brown eyes
Last seen wearing a black button-down, short-sleeved sweater and black pants

120 pounds

The Colorado Bureau of Investigation issued an Amber Alert Sunday night for a 12-year-old boy out of Saguache County.

Sheriff’s officials say Jacob Roe is possibly with 60-year-old David Freeman. They may be traveling in a red 2014 Jeep Patriot with Colorado license plate 198ZQO.

Officials describe Freeman as 5’6 tall, weighing about 135 lbs. Freeman has blue eyes and grey or blonde hair.

If you see Roe, Freeman or the vehicle you are urged to call 911.

snippet.title: Reading and managing amber alerts on an iPhone
snippet.description:
How to read an Amber Alert in the San Francisco Bay Area on an Iphone if you missed the alert the moment it was on your screen.

Also how to turn on and off Amber Alerts and Government Alerts.

On Feb.11th 2014 an Amber alert was sent to the entire San Francisco bay area. In my office I heard the alert on scores of phones. There was a message splashed on the home screen of the phone but seconds later it was gone and there was no apparent way to read it. This video shows you how you can manage getting these messages and how to view it after it was received.

snippet.title: Washington's First Amber Alert
snippet.description:
Sofia Lucerno Juarez disappeared years ago and has never been found. Many people have heard of her case because she was the first child for whom an Amber Alert was issued in the state of Washington. However, far fewer people have heard of the decades-old cold case of Roland Jack Spencer III, who vanished without a trace and has hardly been talked about since. Today, we'll explore both cases of these tragic disappearances, and the lives of these children who were taken too soon.

Sofia Lucerno Juarez: 0:00-10:38
Roland Jack Spencer III: 10:39-16:35

IF YOU HAVE INFORMATION ON SOPHIA, CALL:
1-800-THE-LOST
509-585-4208

IF YOU HAVE INFORMATION ON ROLAND, CALL:
1-800-THE-LOST case #1149796
(509)865.7765
(325)423.2458 (to set up a DNA appointment, NOT for high-priority info)

DISCLAIMER: I do not mean any disrespect in the creation of this video. All of the information presented in the video is information that I have found via a multitude of online sources, all of which are listed towards the end of the video. snippet.title: Authorities Issue Amber Alert In Suspected Kidnapping Of 15 Month Old
snippet.description:
EAST LOS ANGELES (CBSLA) — Authorities issued Amber Alert in suspected abduction of 15-month-old in Boyle Heights.

Authorities say there was a court order made Tuesday for the child to be handed over to Department of Child and Family Services. When DCFS officials showed up to the house in the 2200 block of 4th street near the intersection at St. Louis and 4th, the father and child were gone.

The child’s mother was at LAPD station being questioned however she claims she did not know their whereabouts. Police say she’s being uncooperative.

Police are looking for the boy’s father Carlos Reyna, a 35-year-old Hispanic with black hair, he is 6-foot-2, 200 pounds.

The boy’s name is Noe Reyna

snippet.title: Amber Alert for abducted 11 year old from Peel Region OPP COMMS.  Feb 14-15, 2019
snippet.description:
I was watching youtube as i heard my cell phone make an Amber alert about a missing 11 year old.  I quickly turned on my scanner and recorded.   
The OPP pinged his cell and it last pinged in Pickering at Port Union and 401 hiway around 9pm today.
Later a vehicle driving north on hiway 400 spotted the suspect vehicle in question and OPP came from Barrie and Orillia. townships.
The OPP did a high risk take down.
Vehicle seized and OPP in Communication now with Peel police.

This was an abduction but on the radio the dispatcher advised the suspect is wanted for Homicide.    

Child found dead in a Brampton home.    

Last 10 minutes of the COMMS are quiet but i was recording, you can skip it.   No time to edit.    This is in real time COMMS.


Const. Akil Mooken said the pair were together to celebrate the daughter’s birthday but when the time came to bring her back to the mother, who has custody, they didn’t show up. Comments were made by Rajkumar to the mother indicating he could cause harm to himself and his daughter.

“We have concerns for both Riya and Roopesh,” Mooken said. “We are asking the public for assistance in helping to locate both of these individuals.”

Emergency Management Ontario followed Peel’s original report of the abduction with an emergency alert deployed to mobile devices just after 11:30 p.m.

Police said Roopesh Rajkumar is operating a silver, two-door Honda Civic with a plate number ARBV 598. They were last seen in the area of Hurontario Rd. and Derry Rd. in Mississauga.

Riya Rajkumar is described as brown, four feet, 60 lbs., thin build, with below shoulder length black hair. She was last wearing a pink dress with hearts, black boots, black tights, black jacket with fur-lined hood. She also has a black and white purse with a pink heart that has an R in it.

Peel police have confirmed they working with the Ontario Provincial Police on the investigation.


UPDATE.....

CHILD FOUND DEAD IN A BRAMPTON HOME...
